SIMPLE: mooring
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mooring
<hw>Moor"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of confining a
ship to a particular place, by means of anchors or fastenings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which serves to confine a ship to a place, as
anchors, cables, bridles, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>The place or condition of a ship
thus confined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And the tossed bark in <qex>moorings</qex> swings.</q>
<rj><qau>Moore.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mooring block</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>a heavy
block of cast iron sometimes used as an anchor for mooring
vessels.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moorish</ent>⟦br⟧
